-   <span data-ttu-id="5beec-120">`id` ist "NULL" oder "VOID" oder "GARBAGE".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-120">`id` is "NULL" or "VOID" or "GARBAGE".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="5beec-121">`id` enthält mindestens eine ungültige Regel-ID-Zeichen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-121">`id` contains at least one invalid rule ID character.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-122">Diese Zeichen sind: "?", "\*", "+", "&#124;", "(',')," ^ ","$", '/', ';',". ", '=',"\<"," > "," [","] "," {","} ','\\\\',' ', '\t', '\r' und '\n'.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-122">These characters are: '?', '\*', '+', '&#124;', '(', '), '^', '$', '/', ';', '.', '=', '\<', '>', '[', ']', '{', '}', '\\\\', ' ', '\t', '\r', and '\n'.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-123">Das folgende Beispiel erstellt eine Grammatik, die erkennt den Ausdruck "Es ist ein Staat, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat" gefolgt von den Namen eines Landes, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-123">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-124">Das Beispiel erstellt eine <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Objekt mit dem Namen `winnerRule` auf und übergibt den Bezeichner `WorldCupWinner` als eine <xref:System.String>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-124">The example creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `winnerRule` and passes in the identifier  `WorldCupWinner` as a <xref:System.String>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-125">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> Objekt besteht aus einem Array von neuen <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> Objekten, die alternativen, von der Regel erkannt werden soll.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-125">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object consists of an array of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects containing alternatives to be recognized by the rule.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
