## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-141">Das folgende Beispiel erstellt eine Grammatik, die erkennt den Ausdruck "Es ist ein Staat, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat" gefolgt von den Namen eines Landes, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-141">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-142">Das Beispiel erstellt eine öffentliche Regel, die mit dem Namen `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-142">The example creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-143">Im Beispiel wird dann erstellt zwei <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Objekte `ruleEurope` und `ruleSAmerica`, und übergeben Sie einen <xref:System.String> für die Regel-ID und ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> Array mit einer <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> Objekt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-143">The example then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`, passing in a <xref:System.String> for the rule identifier and an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> array containing a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-144">Im Beispiel wird anschließend Verweise auf lastenausgleichsregeln, `ruleEurope` und `ruleSAmerica` aus der Regel `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-144">Subsequently, the example adds rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` from the rule `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-145">Die erstellte Grammatik hat folgendes Format.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-145">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-153">Typische Ergänzungen zu einer <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Objekt <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, und <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> Objekten, die angeben, was die Lautsprecher sagen können.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-153">Typical additions to an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object include <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> objects that specify what speakers can say.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-154">Ein gültiger Rule-Element muss mindestens ein Teil der erkennbaren Text oder ein Verweis auf eine Regel enthalten.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-154">A valid rule element must contain at least one piece of recognizable text or one rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-155">Finden Sie unter [Erstellen von Grammatiken mithilfe von SrgsGrammar](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361680(v%3doffice.14)) für Weitere Informationen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-155">See [Create Grammars Using SrgsGrammar](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361680(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-156">Ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Objekt enthält möglicherweise auch <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> und <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> Objekte, die die Regel semantische Werte und semantischen Schlüssel hinzu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-156">An <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object may also contain <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects that add semantic values and semantic keys to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-157">Die spracherkennungs-Engine gibt die semantischen Informationen als auch dem erkannten Ausdruck, wenn es erkennt, dass den Ausdruck zurück.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-157">The speech recognition engine will return the semantic information, as well as the recognized phrase, when it recognizes the phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-158">Finden Sie unter [Semantic Markup der Interpretation](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361595(v%3doffice.14)) für Weitere Informationen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-158">See [Semantic Interpretation Markup](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361595(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-159">Das folgende Beispiel erstellt eine Grammatik, die erkennt den Ausdruck "Es ist ein Staat, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat" gefolgt von den Namen eines Landes, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-159">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-160">Nach dem Erstellen der <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Objekt `winnerRule` und ihm den Zeichenfolgenbezeichner `WorldCupWinner`, im Beispiel wird die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> -Methode, um die Zeichenfolge "ein Staat, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat ist" in der Regel.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-160">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method to append the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-161">Im Beispiel wird dann erstellt zwei zusätzliche Regeln, `ruleEurope` und `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-161">The example then creates two additional rules, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-162">Erneut mit der <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> -Methode, um das Beispiel hängt ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> -Objekt an die `WorldCupWinner` Regel, die Verweise auf lastenausgleichsregeln auf enthält `ruleEurope` und `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-162">Again using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to the `WorldCupWinner` rule that contains rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
// and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-192">Der Standardwert für Bereich ist `Private`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-192">The default value for scope is `Private`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-193">Eine private Regel kann nur aktiviert werden für die Erkennung durch einen Verweis auf eine Regel aus der Stammregel in der enthaltenen Grammatik oder aus einer anderen Regel, die von der Stammregel zum verwiesen wird.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-193">A private rule can only be activated for recognition by a rule reference from the root rule in its containing grammar or from another rule that is referenced from the root rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-194">Eine private Regel kann nicht von einer externen Grammatik verwiesen werden, es sei denn, die private Regel als die Stammregel der enthaltenen Grammatik deklariert ist.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-194">A private rule cannot be referenced by an external grammar, unless the private rule is declared as the root rule of its containing grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-195">Wenn der Bereich, um festgelegt ist `Public`, eine <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Objekt kann für die Erkennung aktiviert werden, indem ein Verweis von der eine <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> Objekt in der enthaltenen Grammatik oder von einer Regel in einer externen Grammatik.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-195">If its scope is set to `Public`, an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object can be activated for recognition by a reference from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object in the containing grammar or from a rule in an external grammar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5beec-196">Das folgende Beispiel erstellt eine Grammatik, die erkennt den Ausdruck "Es ist ein Staat, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat" gefolgt von den Namen eines Landes, die die Fußballweltmeisterschaft gewonnen hat.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-196">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5beec-197">Erstellt eine öffentliche Regel, die mit dem Namen `WorldCupWinner` und der Bereich der Regel auf Public festgelegt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5beec-197">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner` and sets the scope of that rule to Public.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope)), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica)})));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```  
  
